# Shopit (An E-commerce Website) 
https://shopit-1-uq3z.onrender.com/

Shopit is an E-commerce website built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React, Node.js), along with Material-UI and Tailwind CSS. 
It follows the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture for a structured and organized development approach.

## Technologies Used
- **Frontend**: React, Material-UI, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js
- **Database**: MongoDB
- **Architecture**: MVC (Model-View-Controller)

## Functionalities

### Customer
- **View Products**: Browse through the list of products available for purchase.
- **Product Details**: View detailed information about each product.
- **Add to Cart**: Select products and add them to the shopping cart.
- **View Cart**: See the list of products added to the cart and view its information by clicking it.
- **Place Order**: Place an order, specifying the quantity of each product and obtaining the calculated price.
- **View Orders**: View a list of previous orders.
- **View Order Details**: Access detailed information about each order with real-time dates of order.

### Retailer
- **Host/Create Products**: Add new products to the website for customers to purchase.
- **Edit Product Info**: Modify the information (e.g., product name, price, description, image, inventory) of existing products.
- **Delete Product**: Remove products from the website's listing.
- **View Sales Stats**: Monitor the number of purchases and profits generated from each product.

### Authorization
- Customers and retailers have separate logins and cannot access each other's pages.

## Database Management
- Products deleted by retailers are automatically removed from user cart, orders, and the home page in the database to maintain data consistency.
- Reduce the number of stock of products based on the orders.
- Products with 0 stocks will not be shown on the home page.

## Website Hosting
The website is hosted at https://shopit-1-uq3z.onrender.com/. Visit the link to explore the functionalities of Shopit.



